GIT COMMANDS:


commands to upload project 1st time into the Git:

cd /path/to/your/project
git init


git add .


git commit -m "Initial commit"


 Create a New Repository on GitHub (or Another Git Hosting Platform)


git remote add origin <repository-url>


git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


If error occurs follow below command again:


git pull origin main --rebase


git rebase --continue


git push -u origin main


2nd commands to follow if you want to pull the code from remote directory:


Assuming the branch already exists remotely:

Switch to the Branch You Want:

git checkout <branch-name>

Pull the Latest Changes:

git pull origin <branch-name>

If the branch doesnâ€™t exist locally, create it and set it to track the remote branch:

git checkout -b <branch-name> 


git branch


git add .


git status


git commit -m "Your commit message"


git push origin cal(branch-name)

